The paper proposes a model for image-text matching that leverages recurrent neural networks (RNN) to process both images and sentences symmetrically. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The model also incorporates attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning for tasks such as language modeling and image captioning, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects, as it deals with matching images and text.
